# Review Checklist

Run this list against your diff before you open or update a PR. The
GitHub PR template carries the user-facing version of it.

## Reuse

- [ ] Did I search `packages/ui/src/components/{primitives,patterns}`
      before writing this?
- [ ] If a near-match existed, did I extend its variants instead of
      forking?
- [ ] Is this component placed at the right tier (L1 / L2 / L3)?

## Tokens & styling

- [ ] No raw hex, `px`, `rgb()`/`hsl()`, or `style={}` outside L1
      primitives.
- [ ] No Tailwind default palette in new code (`gray-*`, `red-*`, etc.).
- [ ] If I added a new value, I added it to `tokens.json` and ran
      `npm run tokens:generate`.
- [ ] `npm run tokens:check` passes.

## Accessibility

- [ ] Keyboard reaches every interactive element in visual order.
- [ ] Visible focus ring on every interactive element.
- [ ] Every interactive element has an accessible name.
- [ ] Touch targets are 44×44 on touch viewports.
- [ ] Form inputs use `FormField` (or equivalent L1) — never bare
      `<input>` in feature code.
- [ ] Errors carry a non-color signal (icon or label).
- [ ] Animations branch on `useReducedMotion()` when > 200ms or
      involving translation.
- [ ] Live regions on data that changes (timers, set counters, async).

## Responsive

- [ ] Verified at `375 × 667`, `768 × 1024`, and `1280 × 800`.
- [ ] No horizontal scroll except intentional carousels.
- [ ] Bottom-pinned primary actions clear the iOS home indicator.
- [ ] In-session UI stays legible in landscape on phones.

## Content

- [ ] Button labels are verb phrases that name the outcome.
- [ ] Errors say what went wrong *and* what to do.
- [ ] Sentence case for buttons, labels, headings.
- [ ] Numbers use `tabular-nums`; weights, time, currency formatted per
      `content-guidelines.md`.

## States

- [ ] Loading, empty, error, loaded states all exist for any fetch
      surface.
- [ ] Async triggers disable + show progress within 100ms.
- [ ] Destructive actions confirm via dialog, not toast.

## Code hygiene

- [ ] No `console.log` (warn/error allowed).
- [ ] No `@ts-ignore` without a comment explaining why.
- [ ] No new dependencies — wrap or extend instead.
- [ ] `npm run lint`, `typecheck`, `test` pass locally.

## PR description

- [ ] UI checklist filled in.
- [ ] Light + dark screenshots (mobile + desktop) attached.
- [ ] Figma frame linked.

If you can't tick a box, explain why in the PR description rather than
ticking it anyway.
